Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.39,0:00:18.36,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:29.82,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.75,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.88,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.81,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:08.70,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.59,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.43,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:36.23,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:29.82,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.75,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.88,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.81,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:08.70,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.59,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.43,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:36.23,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.26,0:01:47.22,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,110)}Ep. 17 - A Tragic Incident
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.50,0:02:09.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.87,0:02:40.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, didn't I tell you before\Nthat you can't leave Marsh's basket here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.23,0:02:41.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.29,0:02:44.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just now, some soil that I've plowed\Nflew this way and hit Marsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.45,0:02:45.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, poor thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.19,0:02:48.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh, please get back inside the basket.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.73,0:02:52.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep hanging around here,\Nmy dear sister might plow you next!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:57.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, thanks for the initiative.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:03:00.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But this way of shoveling won't get you anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.71,0:03:02.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.20,0:03:05.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look at how much we've plowed\Nwhile you were away over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.38,0:03:09.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's still useless. We can't make it into a garden\Nunless you dig a bit deeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.68,0:03:15.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's switch.\NYou go look after Tob, instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.41,0:03:18.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I hate it when I have to babysit Tob.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.98,0:03:20.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh! Marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.39,0:03:22.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, this is no game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.97,0:03:25.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing it because I want our field\Nto be ready sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.44,0:03:27.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that much...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.77,0:03:45.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tob, I won't accept you bullying Marsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.68,0:03:54.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.80,0:03:58.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, try to dig a bit deeper, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.18,0:03:59.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.89,0:04:04.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Because fresh vegetables\Nare so difficult to get in these parts,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.74,0:04:08.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,we've decided to plant\Na vegetable garden behind our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.29,0:04:12.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But because dad was so busy expanding the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.17,0:04:17.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,me and mom ended up fulfilling the duty\Nof planting the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.98,0:04:26.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Jamling, wouldn't you like to rest for a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.76,0:04:30.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No. While we're at it, I'd rather finish this sooner\Nso as to lay the roof sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.86,0:04:33.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I almost feel guilty...\NYou're barely taking any breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.08,0:04:38.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's because I want to be done with it\Nbefore they finish assembling Mr. Pettywell's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.98,0:04:41.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate your determination,\Nbut that's a bit unrealistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.00,0:04:46.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, what they have there is a prefabricated home,\Nwith a crowd of hired workers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.79,0:04:49.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You think the competition is too uneven?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.59,0:04:51.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Ben. Please give me that plank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.43,0:04:54.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. This one?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.69,0:04:55.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.49,0:05:06.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Darn, they seem to be mostly done indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.78,0:05:22.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,While everyone is working with all their might,\NI'm just spending my days away with a cup of tea here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.82,0:05:24.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm truly sorry for being such a burden.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.84,0:05:27.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's about one cup more of tea left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.56,0:05:30.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Oh, thanks but no.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.29,0:05:33.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe there's at least one thing I could go help with?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.97,0:05:37.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As a carpenter, I'm probably good for nothing.\NBut as for planting the garden...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.78,0:05:40.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A doctor doesn't really need\Nto do anything of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.78,0:05:44.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but the thing is, I'm currently a doctor\Nwithout a single patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.20,0:05:47.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, I keep relying on this family's hospitality...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.03,0:05:48.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It starts to rip my heart apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.98,0:05:51.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, "ripping your heart apart?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.37,0:05:54.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You must've been brooding over it quite a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.26,0:05:58.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But actually, both my parents were greatly pleased\Nby you staying at our place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.60,0:06:00.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, I was glad as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.42,0:06:04.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How couldn't I? When living so close to a doctor,\Nyou don't have to worry about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.28,0:06:08.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, I was sure this place\Nwould have at least some folk who are sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.84,0:06:10.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It has.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.29,0:06:14.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that those ill people don't know yet\Nthat a doctor is waiting for them right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.50,0:06:16.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I put out a signboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.22,0:06:19.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Our neighbor Mr. Bernard\Nalso posted a notice at the governor's office,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.39,0:06:23.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,which is supposed to be telling\Nthe town folk about me living here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.59,0:06:26.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's been just three days, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.77,0:06:29.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, you'll see a deluge of patients\Non your doorstep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.69,0:06:31.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope so. I really do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.60,0:06:33.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You will, definitely!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.03,0:06:35.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The inflow of immigrants will only get stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.05,0:06:39.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's summer now, but once the winter comes,\NI'm sure those with weak health would fall ill in droves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.32,0:06:42.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Southern Australia has winter, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.35,0:06:45.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Well, if it has summer,\Nit must have winter, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.59,0:06:51.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you're right... I've never even entertained\Nthe thought of winter coming to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:07:00.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's normal. After all, you never even\Nconsidered staying here in Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.25,0:07:01.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.05,0:07:04.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What was it that made you change your mind\Nand settle in Australia?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.48,0:07:08.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you really had a mind to return to England,\Nyou could board any other ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.02,0:07:09.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.80,0:07:13.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't quite understand it myself,\Nwhy did I decide to settle here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.09,0:07:17.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But at any rate, Australia\Nhad grown on me since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.09,0:07:31.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is good soil.\NI'm sure it'll produce superb vegetables.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.29,0:07:32.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are we sowing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.18,0:07:36.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows.\NI need to confer with your father first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.19,0:07:40.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He'll know which plant\Nwould be the fastest to grow to edible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.19,0:07:42.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're lucky it's summertime.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.00,0:07:45.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The radish that we can eat raw\Nwould probably grow nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.18,0:07:47.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! And we'll be able to eat salad, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.09,0:07:50.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose so. In just forty or fifty days from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.42,0:07:52.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, that long?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.80,0:07:55.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Australia is a land of mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.27,0:07:59.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I really wouldn't mind it growing big enough for eating\Nthe very next day after we sow the seeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.68,0:08:01.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I sure hope it does just that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.37,0:08:04.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.99,0:08:06.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming from that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.60,0:08:10.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't suppose they're laughing at you, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.20,0:08:14.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By Jove, that'd be mighty rude!\NWho could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.00,0:08:16.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's a remarkable vigor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.50,0:08:18.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.00,0:08:23.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There was someone laughing at us just now.\NDidn't you hear anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.68,0:08:25.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Must've been a laughing kookaburra.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.28,0:08:28.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A laughing kookaburra?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.04,0:08:29.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:33.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very odd bird that cries\Nin the morning and the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.88,0:08:36.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was really alike to a human laughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.28,0:08:37.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.69,0:08:40.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When I just moved here,\NI was mighty spooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.33,0:08:44.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But really, that laughing kookaburra\Nonly eats snakes, lizards and frogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.56,0:08:49.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And especially because it also eats poisonous snakes,\Nwe grew to rely heavily on that kind of bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.60,0:08:53.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it,\NLucy-May told us this the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.33,0:08:58.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When a snake was just about to bite her,\Na bird appeared and had that snake for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.30,0:09:01.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And I even called her a liar back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.98,0:09:06.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look after Tob for a moment, sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.78,0:09:09.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, sorry for what I said the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.33,0:09:10.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.97,0:09:13.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Remember when a snake was about to bite you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.24,0:09:15.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you're saying,\Nbut let's postpone it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.95,0:09:19.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh has disappeared!\NLook after Tob, will you?
Comment: 0,0:09:19.18,0:09:20.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.68,0:09:23.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.70,0:09:28.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh! Marsh, come out, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.69,0:09:32.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh! Marsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.80,0:10:29.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.49,0:10:34.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.30,0:10:39.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh, where did you go? Marsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.98,0:10:44.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.90,0:10:47.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.60,0:10:49.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.19,0:11:02.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's crying again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.10,0:11:06.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Australia is rich in some\Nof the most bizarre creatures ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.29,0:11:09.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Have you already seen a platypus, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.79,0:11:11.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Platypus? What is that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.90,0:11:13.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They live by that river.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.93,0:11:17.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I only know about it from my brother's witness,\Nbut I'm yet to see one myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.42,0:11:21.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Does that platypus thing\Nhas this very long kind of beak?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.59,0:11:24.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And it also swims in the river\Nusing those very short legs it has?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.79,0:11:27.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sounds very much like it.\NYou've seen it, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.49,0:11:29.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it near that river.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.68,0:11:31.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Me and Lucy-May did together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.40,0:11:41.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So that was a platypus, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.13,0:11:45.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Say, you're pretty well informed\Nabout the animals' names, aren't you, madam?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.56,0:11:48.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, it's not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.79,0:11:52.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My husband is the one who knows them all,\NI'm merely parroting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.98,0:11:56.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was really glad to learn\Nthat your husband is getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.99,0:11:58.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.00,0:12:02.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, he set out northwards\Non a surveying expedition again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.19,0:12:05.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's all thanks to Doctor Deighton, by Jove!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.88,0:12:11.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That man can be a truly terrific doctor\Nwhenever he is not dead drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.75,0:12:32.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't hurt to have just a mouthful today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.89,0:13:10.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Once we're done with the house,\Nyou'll have to dig a water well next, Mr. Popple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.57,0:13:11.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:12.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.98,0:13:16.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't suppose you know anyone\Nwho can help us dig a well?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.89,0:13:18.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know one such man.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.20,0:13:24.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell me who it is. I can dig it myself for sure,\Nbut it'll take a while if I'm doing it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.28,0:13:25.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.39,0:13:26.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.59,0:13:28.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me also dig the well for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.73,0:13:34.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I guess... I guess it'll be an excellent well\Nif we trust you to dig it for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.40,0:13:36.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm also somehow embarrassed to ask you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.87,0:13:41.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, you're working for half\Nof what Mr. Pettywell was offering you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.80,0:13:44.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, as long as you don't mind doing it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.58,0:13:47.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I accept the request.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.07,0:13:49.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But in exchange, I've one favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.75,0:13:50.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.71,0:13:54.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your goat. I'd like to ask you\Nto give us one of the goatlings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.41,0:13:56.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, those that Lucy-May is keeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.24,0:13:58.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. My son would like to have one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.62,0:14:02.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose, since three of them were born,\Neven Lucy-May would agree
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.46,0:14:05.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,that yielding just one to your son\Nis not a big deal at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.89,0:14:08.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, I'll try to talk\Nwith Lucy-May about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.84,0:14:10.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks a bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.09,0:14:14.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no. I got so engrossed in talking,\NI completely forgot about the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.51,0:14:18.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If this keeps up, we'll end up\Nletting Mr. Pettywell open up a lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.00,0:14:30.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How do you like this? Give it just a week more\Nand we'll be living in a real house.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.37,0:14:33.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It'd better be the fanciest house\Nin the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.45,0:14:34.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.89,0:14:39.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To build a house fancier than this, one would have\Nto desperately scramble for only the best materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.43,0:14:43.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And even then, it'll take them no less\Nthan four or five months to assemble it. No, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.98,0:14:46.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you quite sure it'll be ready in a week?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.15,0:14:48.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... That's what the workmen told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.55,0:14:50.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm asking you, not them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.63,0:14:53.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't building it myself, y'know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.40,0:14:55.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I am decisively fed up with living in a tent!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.97,0:14:57.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to promise me
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.43,0:15:00.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,that this house would be completed\Nin just a week more!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.12,0:15:01.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. I promise, alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.69,0:15:05.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, I'm going on a promenade\Nthrough the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.52,0:15:06.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.48,0:15:08.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No need to answer me twice!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.12,0:15:08.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.26,0:15:10.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Have a nice walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.91,0:15:11.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.92,0:15:13.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.01,0:15:15.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to do\Nabout the water well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.99,0:15:18.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The well is usually being dug\Nafter the house is completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.77,0:15:21.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,For the time being,\Nwe should prioritize assembling the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.47,0:15:24.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The water that they draw\Nfrom the river is all mucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.16,0:15:25.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.32,0:15:26.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then build a well to solve it please!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.86,0:15:28.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, give it just a week more...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.73,0:15:29.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We need it right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.77,0:15:32.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How can you say that,\Nwhen we've no workers to spare...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.20,0:15:33.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Workers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.39,0:15:34.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.49,0:15:35.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uh? What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.10,0:15:37.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is your role in this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.87,0:15:40.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You're asking what my role is,\Nwell, that's quite...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.32,0:15:42.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just settle on you digging the well yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.10,0:15:46.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can't ask me to do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.66,0:15:54.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.61,0:15:56.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be so cruel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.18,0:16:01.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it me who has to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.62,0:16:04.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Hey, tell me why!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.99,0:16:53.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? They're not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.09,0:16:58.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.66,0:17:04.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? You guys chose to hang around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.61,0:17:09.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you know it's rude to bother Dr. Deighton\Nduring his afternoon nap?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.08,0:17:14.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're a cute thing, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.77,0:17:16.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Billy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.78,0:17:17.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.80,0:17:19.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.78,0:17:23.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, your goats wandered all the way to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.08,0:17:27.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, got! Got!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.89,0:17:35.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Hey, Sticky!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.88,0:17:51.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That must've been how they got out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.18,0:17:53.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, in you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.87,0:17:56.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You too, 'cos you're good kids, aintcha?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.38,0:18:09.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Billy, I'll give you one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.90,0:18:10.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.90,0:18:12.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You said you wanted a goatling.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.79,0:18:15.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:19.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Remember I said I'll give you one\Nif you catch for me that animal sitting on top of the tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.76,0:18:21.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I never caught any.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.64,0:18:24.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But you'll catch one for me one day, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.69,0:18:27.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! I'll break my neck to catch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.60,0:18:30.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm letting you\Nhave one of baby goats now already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.44,0:18:32.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.34,0:18:33.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.05,0:18:37.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I think it'd be better if we let them\Ndrink Sticky's milk for a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.69,0:18:41.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's true, alright.\NBut... Are you really letting me have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.87,0:18:44.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Consider one of them yours already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.11,0:18:46.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,T-thank you, Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.21,0:18:48.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now... Which one should I choose?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.34,0:18:51.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Isn't there supposed to be one more?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.41,0:18:53.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.39,0:18:59.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably still in the tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.78,0:19:13.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The goatling doesn't seem to be in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.20,0:19:18.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Billy! There's Mr. Pettywell's black dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.08,0:19:25.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Billy! Hurry up!\NIt's about to grab the goatling!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:31.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.60,0:19:47.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.38,0:20:03.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Billy, what happened to the goatling?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.58,0:20:08.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Please tell me the goatling is alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.52,0:20:11.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.56,0:20:13.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.08,0:20:16.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.70,0:20:23.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, screw you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.20,0:20:27.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How about this?\NI can do something useful, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.87,0:20:31.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can even dig a well alright\Nif you set your mind to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.78,0:20:33.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn! Damn! Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.59,0:20:35.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.67,0:20:40.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.06,0:20:43.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you've done\Nsomething stupid again!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.08,0:20:45.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll know right away if you have!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.29,0:20:49.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can bet this fellow\Nwill always be good-for-nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.21,0:20:49.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.98,0:20:54.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!\NIt hurts! Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.89,0:20:57.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Man, my back hurts so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.19,0:21:02.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Happy! Don't be such a bloody eyesore!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.90,0:21:05.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Screw you! Ouch! Ouch-ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.10,0:21:07.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.98,0:21:12.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, they ain't having it good\Nwhen bitten in this part of the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.00,0:21:17.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The viciousness of this dog knows no bounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.89,0:21:22.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go and tell Mr. Pettywell\Neverything I think about him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.90,0:21:25.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even giving him a mouthful\Nwon't bring this goatling back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.78,0:21:31.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it's not like Mr. Pettywell\Ndeliberately ordered it to slaughter the goatling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.42,0:21:34.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That black dog is getting my hardest kick\Nnext time we meet!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.10,0:21:37.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is in Mr. Pettywell himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.18,0:21:41.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dogs always take after their owners!\NThat dog is Mr. Pettywell's spitting image!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.56,0:21:43.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Only ever being violent and mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.61,0:21:44.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Stop with that talk, Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.60,0:21:46.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.96,0:21:56.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ma'am! Ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.46,0:21:59.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Master is in big trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.31,0:22:00.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.36,0:22:03.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He fell into the pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.48,0:22:04.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Into the pit?
Comment: 0,0:22:06.81,0:22:08.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.30,0:22:11.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world has happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.19,0:22:13.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He said he can't get out of the pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.78,0:22:16.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?\NFrom a hole that tiny?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.00,0:22:21.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well. I suppose it's impressive\Nfor something you've dug all by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.49,0:22:24.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But what is it with you being unable to exit that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.34,0:22:29.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's my back. My back hurts so much\NI can't move at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.31,0:22:30.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your back?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.48,0:22:37.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Whenever I move even a little,\Nit hurts so much I think I could die! Ouch! Ouch, ouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.13,0:22:39.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How should we handle this, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.10,0:22:41.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you intend to live in this hole\Nfor the rest of your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.81,0:22:45.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's this nonsense... Ouch! Ouch-ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.58,0:22:51.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, I beg you. We need you\Nto come see him in that hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.20,0:22:54.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's a mole now, huh?\NDoes it really hurt that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.07,0:22:58.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He won't allow anyone to come near him\Nand just keeps shouting, "Hurts! It hurts!"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.42,0:23:01.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Well, I guess the divine punishment\Ncaught up with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.40,0:23:02.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.12,0:23:05.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, don't mind me.\NNow, let's start with the examination.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.59,0:23:09.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm goin' out, folk!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.79,0:23:12.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you, it's a strained back. Strained back!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.68,0:23:21.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think it'd be perfectly fine for him\Nto refuse to see Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.01,0:23:22.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It definitely would!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.78,0:23:24.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He is bound by the doctor's oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.79,0:23:28.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which means even if it's the most spiteful\Nenemy of our parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.16,0:23:31.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,the doctor is obliged to examine him\Nwhenever he is in pain.
